data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will get a numeric suffix appended. Pin with:

```csharp
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
```

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to `BillingAddress_City` but now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. Pin with `HasColumnName()` to preserve the old name, or accept the rename and generate a migration.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Add `string logCommandText` to every method:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    { /* logging — use logCommandText for safe log output */ }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
